figgy.title: BrowseEverything fails to read from Folders which are shared with users (but for which the users themselves are not owners)

comments.body: Queries passed to the Google Drive API need to have two parenthetical components which enable both shared drives to be queried, or one's own personal drive. This is structured in a manner such as `(sharedWithMe and parents = 'folder-id') or (parents = 'folder-id')`.

https://github.com/jrgriffiniii/browse-everything/compare/figgy-issues-3201-jrgriffiniii...jrgriffiniii:figgy-issues-3522-jrgriffiniii has gotten the queries split between both, but I need to adjust the syntax for searching in parent folders.

https://github.com/jrgriffiniii/browse-everything/compare/figgy-issues-3201-jrgriffiniii...jrgriffiniii:figgy-issues-3522-jrgriffiniii#diff-d11ac98056a1350e27c0de30499432a3R130 still retrieves all shared Folders, including the children of shared Folders which have not been selected from the root path.
https://github.com/jrgriffiniii/browse-everything/commit/a42ab8a5fac2d1558c667248228c6dc2da9840bb gets shared Folder browsing working as required.

After deploying https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/compare/issues-3522-jrgriffiniii-browse-everything-shared into the staging environment, I am now successfully able to browse the contents of a shared Folder:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/70641448-9f3cc780-1c0b-11ea-85fe-39605411614b.png)
